In the discussion on making access to abortion a human right, the argument that legalisation would simply increase the number of abortions does not hold. CAFOD was instrumental in the UK government response to the International Conference on Population and Development which took place in Nairobi in 1994. The UK government already provides financial support to developing countries to meet with their population targets and has now approved aid to provide access to legal abortion for women in developing countries.
